<p>The majority of programs that we write will need to be more than a single sequential path of execution. We usually work with data that isnâ€™t always the same, and occasionally requires us to do different things based on that data. To achieve this we need to utilize conditionals. In this hands-on lab, weâ€™ll work through the conditional logic for the popular interviewing Fizz-Buzz problem by creating a script that will prompt the user for a number and then print out either the number, â€œFizzâ€, â€œBuzzâ€, or â€œFizzBuzzâ€ depending on whether the number meets one of the Fizz-Buzz requirements.</p>

