<h2 id="the-scenario">The Scenario</h2>

<p>A typical Fizz-Buzz problem goes like this:</p>

<p>Write a program that prints the numbers from 1 - 100. For each multiple of three print â€œFizzâ€ instead of the number. For multiples of five print â€œBuzzâ€ instead of the number. If a number is a multiple of three and five then print â€œFizzBuzzâ€.</p>

<p>Solving this problem requires 2 key components: looping and conditionals. Weâ€™re going to write a simplified program only using the conditional portion that will take any given number that we provide and print the Fizz-Buzz value. Hereâ€™s how it will work:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ ./fizz-buzz-item.py
