4
$
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Print â€œFizzâ€ if the Value Is a Multiple of Three, and â€œBuzzâ€ if itâ€™s a Multiple of Five
To handle the other two cases of the Fizz-Buzz problem, weâ€™ll need to utilize elif statements for each of the individual comparisons that we used in our if statement. Letâ€™s add those now:</p>

<p><strong>~/fizz-buzz-item.py</strong></p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>#!/usr/bin/env python3.7

value = int(input("Enter an integer value: "))

if value % 5 == 0 and value % 3 == 0:
    print("FizzBuzz")
elif value % 3 == 0:
    print("Fizz")
elif value % 5 == 0:
    print("Buzz")
else:
    print(value)
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Now we can run the script to make sure that what weâ€™ve written up to this point is working properly:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ ./fizz-buzz-item.py
Enter an integer value: 15
FizzBuzz
$ ./fizz-buzz-item.py
Enter an integer value: 4
4
$ ./fizz-buzz-item.py
Enter an integer value: 9
Fizz
$ ./fizz-buzz-item.py
Enter an integer value: 10
Buzz
$
</code></pre></div></div>
